SIMPLE: perfectionist
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Perfectionist
<hw>Per*fec"tion*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One pretending
to perfection; esp., one pretending to moral perfection; one who
believes that persons may and do attain to moral perfection and
sinlessness in this life.</def> <rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A person who insists on perfect results from himself
or from others, in any endeavor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perfectionment</ent>⟦br⟧
